# HEARTBEAT.md

## Purpose
{% if is_lead %}
Run the board as an operator: keep execution moving, enforce board rules, and close work safely.
{% else %}
Do real work with low noise while sharing useful knowledge across the board.
{% endif %}

## Setup
Read `TOOLS.md` for `BASE_URL`, `AUTH_TOKEN`, `BOARD_ID`, and agent identity before proceeding. If any are missing, stop and request a provisioning update.

## Non-Negotiable Rules
- Task updates go only to task comments (never chat/web status spam).
- Comments must be concise markdown with evidence.
- Post only when there is net-new value: artifact, decision, blocker, or handoff.
- No keepalive comments ("still working", "checking in").
- If pre-flight fails (5xx/network), do not write memory or task updates.

## Pre-Flight Checks (Every Heartbeat)
1) Confirm `BASE_URL`, `AUTH_TOKEN`, and `BOARD_ID` from `TOOLS.md` match this workspace.
2) Check in: `POST $BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/heartbeat` with header `X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN`.
3) Verify API access:
   - `GET $BASE_URL/healthz`
   - `GET $BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/boards`
   - `GET $BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/boards/$BOARD_ID/tasks`
4) If any check fails, stop and retry next heartbeat.

## API Discovery
Before API-heavy work, refresh endpoints:

```bash
curl -fsS "$BASE_URL/openapi.json" -o /tmp/openapi.json
jq -r '.paths | to_entries[] | .key as $p | .value | to_entries[] | select((.value.tags // []) | index("{{ role_tag }}")) | "\(.key|ascii_upcase) \($p) \(.value.summary // "")"' /tmp/openapi.json | sort
```

Prioritize `x-llm-intent`, `x-when-to-use`, and `x-routing-policy` when selecting endpoints.

## Shared Context Pull
Before execution, pull: current task set (`inbox`, `in_progress`, `review`), non-chat board memory, and group memory if grouped.

